content.description: Start with large wavey ledge and pull up to top.
content.location: On the north end of the North Shore. Directly right of Emily’s Chimney (V-Easy).

content.description: Start on Jameson Arete, and move left onto the ledges on the face.
An eliminate that avoids using the crack to the left and the holds of Earth Mechanics (V5) to the right. A hard sit start leads to big moves and sharp crimps.
content.location: On the north end of the North Shore. Immediately right of a large crack that separates this and Horseshoes and Hand Grenades (V2); directly left of Earth Mechanics (V5).

content.description: The obvious chimney between Emily's Naptime and V1 Face. A good choice for scoping Emily's Naptime.
content.location: 1. North Shore between Emily's Naptime and V1 Face.

content.description: Low ball traverse from left to right.  SDS as far left as possible and traverse right using good edges over the lip and small low feet.  Top out over far right end.  Named after my youngest daughter shortly after her birth.  Not sure if its V1 or not but didn't want to show favoritism for this problem over the one named after my other daughter... Parents will understand!
content.location: On the north end of the North Shore. Directly below Horseshoes and Hand Grenades (V2).

content.description: Climb up arete using anything you can, very tricky for the grade.
content.location: On the north end of the North Shore. The arete between Oil Can (V1) and Emily’s Naptime (V1+)

content.description:
Climb 14 feet on thin face holds avoiding the ledge to the right. The ledges to avoid have red arrows pointing to them in the picture. Spotting someone climbing below the upper blocks is no problem, but if you fall above that you'll have some problems landing as there are small jagged boulders on a small hill directly behind you - likely to be an ankle snap. One of my favorite boulder routes.\

 On the north end of the North Shore. The first problem on the northernmost stretch of rock.
The chunky outside corner and chimney. A beginner's scamper or down-climb.
content.location: On the north end of the North Shore. Around the arete from Earth Mechanics (V5); to the left of Oil Can (V1)

content.description: Climb up using the arete to the left and the crack to the right.
content.location: On the north end of the North Shore. In between Jameson Arete (V3) to the left and the dihedral that holds Emily’s Chimney (V-Easy) to the right.

content.description: Start low in face on large sidepull and climb your way up and out left on thin holds.
content.location: On the north end of the North Shore. Immediately right of Sheriff's Approval (V5).

content.description: Climb up corner with interesting start.
content.location: On the north end of the North Shore. The final problem (rightmost) on the northernmost stretch of rock in the area; directly right of V1 Face (V1).

content.description: Just a few steps from the parking lot, the Earth Mechanics stretch of rock provides a number of easy to moderate problems varying in style. Most of which are fairly tall with relatively flat landings.
